# Our Development Rules

These are our "laws." They'll keep the project healthy.

## Rule 1: The app should always build

Do not leave the project in a broken build state. Fix build errors before finishing work.

## Rule 2: The app should always run

Changes must not break the running app. Verify the app still starts and core flows work.

## Rule 3: Every feature gets committed separately

One feature per commit. Do not bundle unrelated changes into a single commit.

## Rule 4: Never hard-code event data

Load event data from configuration, APIs, or data files — not inline in source code.

## Rule 5: Document every major decision

Record significant architectural and product choices in `docs/`.

## Rule 6: Keep the interface simple

A volunteer should be able to learn the UI in under five minutes. Prefer clarity over complexity.
